top_reviews.title: Not showing total 128 Gb space
top_reviews.body: I have purchased 128 Gb SD card for my Samsung Galaxy A7 (2019) Android mobile phone. Today its gt delivered. When i inserted it on my mobile, its showing only 119 Gb total Space instead of 128 Gb. To cross check, i tried in card reader and connect it to laptop, but then also its showing total space as 119 Gb instead of 128 Gb. Immediately I requested for replacement. Let's see how i will get the replacement and whether that product quality is accurate or not.Read more
top_reviews.body_html:
I have purchased 128 Gb SD card for my Samsung Galaxy A7 (2019) Android mobile phone.
Today its gt delivered.
When i inserted it on my mobile, its showing only 119 Gb total Space instead of 128 Gb.
To cross check, i tried in card reader and connect it to laptop, but then also its showing total space as 119 Gb instead of 128 Gb.
Immediately I requested for replacement.
Let's see how i will get the replacement and whether that product quality is accurate or not.

top_reviews.title: Received a genuine product. Other card makers offer better performance at about the same price.
top_reviews.body: The product I received seems to be genuine. I ran some tests which showed that there was a full 128 GB (more like 121 GB) of storage. However, sequential read/writes and also random reads/writes are abysmal at less than 100 MB/s read and a rather disappointing less than 50 MB/s write. Speeds are nowhere near the advertised speeds. I should've gone for Samsung EVO 128 GB which is a UHS 3 capable card at about the same price(as of today). Also, I see a lot of people expecting a full 128 GB capacity to be available, however, for all storage devices expensive or cheap, there will always be partitioning and file system overhead, coupled with how the computer actually reads the capacity (as 1024 units and not 1000 units). So in reality, a 119 GB or 121 GB shown is perfectly normal.  Although it serves the purpose well and has lasted me many months of continuous heavy use on my dashcam without any hitches, I would not recommend it if there are other products available at about the same price.Read more

top_reviews.title: For the price it is VERY fair performer.
top_reviews.body: Came already formated in exFAT with 238gb of free space.  Speeds were tested on a sub 3.0 hub connected to the computer which is more than enough able to stress the card.  Read speed is a bit far from advertise speed at 97mb/s. Not even in the 3 digits, but close. Although nobody will feel the difference between 97 and 120 unless you're using it to browse a massive library of picture and even then it should be a small difference.  Write speed are a bit slow though at 36 mb/sec. But, his is just a U1 with a minimum speed of 10mb/sec and perform like a U3 over 30mb/sec, but when comparing it to the read speed, it's closer to 1/3 of the speed.  For application use, the IOPS count get more important. The A1 specs ask for 1500 iops read and 500 iops write and a minimum of 10mb/sec sequential write (do NOT compare it with computer hardware where for example my NVME Samsung 980 pro 2TB give 120 000 read and 97 000 write in iops ). Here once again the card deliver with about 2400 iops read and 710 write which is above specs and with the 36mb/sec sequential write fill the specs.  In conclusion, this is a card advertise to be a U1, A1, so in the bottom of the classes of micro SD nowadays and is represented by the price, which is one of the least expensive card in the reputable manufacturers you can get. The "reputable" part come with the 10 years warranty from Sandisk and the long lasting reputation of the company in media storage. The card although deliver more than what is advertised in a lot of fields since it perform like a U3 and is close to twice the specs of the A1 class.  This card is intended to increase the raw storage of a device but not as a powerhouse of transfer. It will be perfect to extend your phone or tablet storage, but might rush a little bit to run a lot of application from it. If you adopt it for picture and video storage and use the onboard memory for applications this is a very good choice.Read more
